title: Web Developer
description:
PHP Developer :

Job Description :

The role is responsible for creating and implementing an array of Web-based products using PHP, MySQL, Ajax, and JavaScript. You develop back-end components, connect the application with other web services, and assist front-end developers by ensuring their work integrates with the application.

Responsibilities :

1) Conducting analysis of website and application requirements.

2) Writing back-end code and building efficient PHP modules.

3) Developing back-end portals with an optimized database.

4) Troubleshooting application and code issues.

5) Integrating data storage solutions.

6) Responding to integration requests from front-end developers.

7) Finalizing back-end features and testing web applications.

8) Updating and altering application features to enhance performance.

SKILLS :

Knowledge of PHP web frameworks including Laravel, and CodeIgniter.

Knowledge of front-end technologies including CSS3, JavaScript, and HTML5.

Understanding of... object-oriented PHP programming.

To create robust and scalable applications

title: Full Stack Web Developer
description:
We are looking for a Full Stack Developer to produce scalable software solutions. You'll be part of a cross-functional team that's responsible for the full software development life cycle, from conception to deployment. As a Full Stack Developer, you should be comfortable around both front-end and back-end coding languages, development frameworks and third-party libraries. You should also be a team player with a knack for visual design and utility.

Bachelor of Science (B.Sc)

title: Web Developer
description:
POSITION

Web Services Developer

LOCATION

Genworth India

POSITION SUMMARY

Position will be responsible for developing micro and meshed web services to Genworth’s admin systems, and will be working in an agile team building a unified desktop experience for our customer service representatives. The position reports to the Enterprise Services group, building upon the Java web services platform.

RESPONSIBILITIES
• Lead and/or participate in the analysis and design efforts in support of application and business requirements. Design within the architectural and system strategy constraints.
• Understand and apply accepted application development and integration processes in all development activities. Actively participate in efforts to improve existing processes.
• Work closely with internal business partners to resolve problems and escalate issues to leadership when necessary.
• Drive improvement to the application architecture, workshop new development patterns
• Ability to stay... abreast of emerging technology and integration best practices, and apply those best practices in our environment.

REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS
• Languanges
• Java
• Python
• Go
• 3 Years Professional Experience
• Kubernetes
• Docker
• Web Services, Spring, Spring Boot

PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS
• Service API Development
• AWS EC2
• Rancher
• Agile
• Continuous Integration/Deployment
• Git
• JUNIT/Unit Testing
• Splunk

title: Web Developer wordpress
description:
The Website Developer will work in collaboration with our marketing team to develop and maintain high-quality, stand out and engaging websites.

We have currently 4 word press sites. This is work from home part time opportunity for our Mortgage business and disability business sector in Australia.

Job Description :-
• Seek or provide guidance in working closely with the team to ensure only the highest quality content and design are produced.
• Design, develop and test new functionality to add to our existing websites.
• Design, develop and add new content to the website such as animation, promotions, product updates, online enquiry tools, etc.
• Developing new websites using WordPress.
• Research and troubleshoot software and development issues and work with the team to provide solutions.
• Work with our internal teams, build, test and deploy new features and fixes across our websites
• Take care of both front-end and back-end development.

Key responsibilities:
• Research and... analyze advertising competitors.
• Manage the expense and budget of campaigns, and estimate monthly costs.
• Develop drive the companies digital strategy.
• Stay up to date with trends and technologies within the digital marketing world.
• Develop, implement, and manage digital marketing campaigns that promote the products of a company and deliver sales.
• Ensure a high quality and consistent service delivery across the whole digital marketing campaign.

Desired Candidate Profile
• Good Communication skill Written/ Verbal
• Qualifications in website development technologies, software engineering, or other related field.
• 3+ years’ experience as a website developer
• Ability to code, test and debug in JavaScript, jQuery, CSS scripting, and web technologies (HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, PHP, MySQL).
• Good working knowledge of HTML (including mobile responsiveness),
• Experience with using a CMS platform such as WordPress.
• Knowledge of AI framework
• A good understanding of Google Analytics, goal tracking and SEO

Benefits:
• Flexible working hours work from home
• Great work/life balance and lifestyle
• Stable, long-term employment.

Work Remotely
• Yes

Job Types: Full-time, Part-time, Regular / Permanent

Part-time hours: 30 per week

Salary: ₹17,000.00 - ₹25,947.00 per month

Job Type: Part-time
Part-time hours: 20 per week

Salary: ₹15,006.96 - ₹20,416.50 per month

Schedule:
• Day shift
• Flexible shift

Supplemental pay types:
• Performance bonus

Education:
• Bachelor's (Required)

Experience:
• wordpress: 3 years (Required)

Work Location: Remote

Application Deadline: 03/06/2023
Expected Start Date: 05/06/2023

title: Back End Developer
description:
Responsibilities
• Participate in the entire application lifecycle, focusing on coding and debugging
• Write clean code to develop functional web applications
• Troubleshoot and debug applications
• Perform UI tests to optimize performance
• Manage cutting-edge technologies to improve legacy applications
• Collaborate with Front-end developers to integrate user-facing elements with server side logic
• Gather and address technical and design requirements
• Provide training and support to internal teams
• Build reusable code and libraries for future use
• Liaise with developers, designers and system administrators to identify new features
• Follow emerging technologies

Requirements and skills
• In-depth understanding of the entire web development process (design, development and deployment)
• Hands on experience with programming languages like JavaScript, PHP.
• At least two years' experience as a Node.js developer.
• Extensive knowledge of JavaScript, web stacks, libraries, and... frameworks.
• Familiarity with front-end languages (e.g. HTML, JavaScript and CSS)
• Excellent analytical and time management skills
• Teamwork skills with a problem-solving attitude
• BSc degree in Computer Science or relevant field

title: Frontend Developer
description:
About This Role

As a Front End Developer you will be responsible for translating the CMS design requirements such as figma to technical designs which includes enterprise-level architecture and implementing strategies using components of the CMS(Wordpress and Optimizely) to support multi-site, multi-channel, multi-lingual delivery environments.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
• Partner with web developers, engineers, marketers, and designers to scale Zoom’s web production
• Collaborate with product managers, engineers, web developers, visual designers, and business stakeholders to create custom web pages for global product launches, marketing campaigns, events, and promotions.
• Develop Digital Consumer experiences using front end technologies such as HTML/JS/Jquery/React.
• Work with architects to ensure that scalable solutions are created, alongside equally talented CMS engineers.
• Should be able to create templates based on standard SEO standards.
• Diagnose and solve technical problems... related to content management implementation.
• Conduct code reviews for ongoing projects to ensure optimal code quality and appropriate design patterns are used.
• Participate in project planning sessions with team members to analyze development requirements, provide work breakdown and estimates of work

QUALIFICATIONS
• 4 plus years of creating user experience using front end technology(HTML5, CSS and JS library).
• Expert level development skills using REST, Javascript, jQuery, AJAX, JSON, HTML, CSS, NodeJS and angularJS.
• Experience with MVC based application development will have great add.
• Experience migrating from existing CMS to Optimizely is a plus
• Javascript Frameworks - preferred but not required
• AngularJS v4+/React or any other JS Framework.
• Good understanding of content management systems.
• Good understanding of search engine optimization principles.
• Knowledge of version control systems such as github or gitlab is a plus.
• Ability to troubleshoot the code issues and recommend solutions.

We believe that the unique contributions of all Zoomies is the driver of our success. To make sure that our products and culture continue to incorporate everyone's perspectives and experience we never discriminate on the basis of race, religion, national origin, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, age, or marital, veteran, or disability status. Zoom is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.

We welcome people of different backgrounds, experiences, abilities and perspectives including qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records and any qualified applicants requiring reasonable accommodations in accordance with the law. If you need any assistance or accommodations due to a medical condition, or if you need assistance accessing our website or completing the application process, please let us know by emailing us at careers@zoom.us.

At Zoom, we care about our employees, their families, and their well-being. As part of our award-winning workplace culture and commitment to delivering happiness, our benefits program offers a variety of perks, benefits, and options to help employees maintain their physical, mental, emotional, and financial health; support work-life balance; and contribute to their community in meaningful ways. To view our benefits, click here.

Work Styles at Zoom

In most cases, you will have the opportunity to choose your preferred working location from the following options when you join Zoom: in-person, hybrid or remote. Visit this page for more information about Zoom's Workstyles.

About Us

Zoomies help people stay connected so they can get more done together. We set out to build the best video product for the enterprise, and today help people communicate better with products like Zoom Contact Center, Zoom Phone, Zoom Events, Zoom Apps, Zoom Rooms, and Zoom Webinars.

We’re problem-solvers, working at a fast pace to design solutions with our customers and users in mind. Here, you’ll work across teams to deliver impactful projects that are changing the way people communicate and enjoy opportunities to advance your career in a diverse, inclusive environment.

• Browse Awards and Employee Reviews on Comparably
• Visit our Blog
• Zoom with us!
• Find us on social at the links below and on Instagram
• View more jobs, sign up for job alerts and join our talent community. Visit the Zoom careers site
